    ('pcm-motivation-167', 'Best Ways to Prepare', 'Complete the most important topics first; perfection in one chapter cannot compensate for ignoring five others.', 166),
    ('pcm-motivation-168', 'Best Ways to Prepare', 'Simulate examination conditions before examination day becomes your first full simulation.', 167),
    ('pcm-motivation-169', 'Best Ways to Prepare', 'The best preparation leaves fewer surprises—not because you know every question, but because you can handle unfamiliar ones.', 168),
    ('pcm-motivation-170', 'Mindset on Exam Day', 'Enter the examination hall to execute your preparation, not to judge your future.', 169),
    ('pcm-motivation-171', 'Mindset on Exam Day', 'A calm first five minutes can protect the next three hours.', 170),
    ('pcm-motivation-172', 'Mindset on Exam Day', 'Read the entire paper with curiosity, not fear. Fear makes you confused', 171),
    ('pcm-motivation-173', 'Mindset on Exam Day', 'Begin with confidence, continue with discipline and finish with verification.', 172),
    ('pcm-motivation-174', 'Mindset on Exam Day', 'Do not decide that a paper is difficult before you have identified the questions you can solve.', 173),
    ('pcm-motivation-175', 'Mindset on Exam Day', 'One challenging section does not define the whole examination.', 174),
    ('pcm-motivation-176', 'Mindset on Exam Day', 'Your task is not to know everything; it is to earn every mark available from what you know.', 175),
    ('pcm-motivation-177', 'Mindset on Exam Day', 'Breathe deep before reacting to an unfamiliar question.', 176),
    ('pcm-motivation-178', 'Mindset on Exam Day', 'On exam day, trust your preparation more than your anxiety.', 177),
    ('pcm-motivation-179', 'Mindset on Exam Day', 'Do not borrow panic from students discussing answers outside the examination hall.', 178),
    ('pcm-motivation-180', 'Mindset on Exam Day', 'Keep moving when stuck; returning with a calmer mind often reveals the method.', 179),
    ('pcm-motivation-181', 'Mindset on Exam Day', 'Check signs, units, question numbers and final answers before submitting.', 180),
    ('pcm-motivation-182', 'Mindset on Exam Day', 'A temporary blank mind is a signal to pause, breathe and retrieve—not to panic.', 181),
    ('pcm-motivation-183', 'Mindset on Exam Day', 'Save enough time to review the answers that carry the most marks.', 182),
    ('pcm-motivation-184', 'Mindset on Exam Day', 'Leave the examination hall with lessons, not endless rechecking of what cannot be changed. This will help you prepare for your next exam day', 183),
    ('pcm-motivation-185', 'Mindset on Exam Day', 'The best exam-day mindset is simple: one question, one decision and one careful step at a time.', 184)
